For years, tedious comedians traded on the stereotype of women being bad drivers who couldn t read maps. The actual source of motorway enmity is that a large number of men are hypertense control-freaks with hair-trigger emotions who spiral into an anxiety attack the second that they don t know exactly where they are, if they re on the right road or precisely how many metres it is to the next Little Chef.45 minutes into the journey and any other-half in their right mind would be excused for popping the catch, rolling out of a moving vehicle like Jason Statham and taking their chances on the hard shoulder.&nbsp;